OL,6,FThe court heard a failure by Pirelli
OL,7,FTyres, DCS and IRTR to co-ordinate
OL,8,Ftheir approach to risk management
OL,9,Fmeant no company took responsibility
OL,10,Ffor the dangerous work activity.
OL,12,FAs a result, there was a failure to
OL,13,Frisk assess the task with any attempt
OL,14,Fto eliminate or control the dangers
OL,15,Fcreated being missed.
OL,17,FPirelli, and IRTR, admitted two health
OL,18,Fand safety law breaches, while DCS,
OL,19,Fadmitted one breach.
